comments: Rozier (CHA) and Siakam (TOR) mutually engage and disengage with one another as they each attempt to establish post position.
Miller (CHA) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends the pass intended for Anunoby (TOR) in the corner.

Schroder (TOR) and Bridges (CHA) come together at the same spot during the drive and marginal contact occurs as Schroder releases away from Bridges, whose momentum continues to carry him further into the lane.

Replay review of the foul called on Hayward (CHA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  The contact between Hayward (CHA) and Anunoby (TOR) is marginal, and then Anunoby moves through Richsards' (CHA) space and dislodges him from his screening position.  There is no foul on Hayward and a foul is assessed to Anunoby.
Siakam (TOR) brings his hands toward Rozier's (CHA) back and marginal contact occurs as Siakam releases away to roll.
Richards (CHA) brings his right hand forward toward Barnes' (TOR) back and marginal contact occurs after Barnes starts his upward shooting motion.

Anunoby (TOR) maintains a rested hand on Miller's (CHA) side and marginal contact occurs after Miller's gather. Anunoby then makes incidental "high-five" contact with Miller after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Rozier's (CHA) hands come forward toward Schroder's (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs with Schroder's front at the top of the perimeter.
Hayward's (CHA) left hand comes forward prior to marginal contact occurring with Barnes' (TOR) front as Barnes passes.
Richards (CHA) and Siakam (TOR) mutually engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Rozier's (CHA) off-arm is brought outward slightly when he and Barnes (TOR) come together at the same spot during the drive, and marginal contact occurs as Rozier releases away toward the wing.
Rozier (CHA) gathers the ball on his right foot before taking two steps into his jump shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) is jumping to Rozier's (CHA) side and would avoid Rozier if Rozier did not slightly extend his right leg outward to initiate the marginal contact.
Barnes (TOR) re-establishes slightly following the initial contact with Rozier (CHA) during the pick and further marginal contact occurs prior to Rozier moving underneath it.

Replay review of the foul called on Rozier (CHA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Rozier steps into Barnes's (TOR) space and illegal foot contact occurs as he returns to the floor and the foul stands as called.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Rozier (CHA).
Washington (CHA) avoids making contact with Barnes (TOR) and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
